rComments: Very supportive of students. Although slightly disorganised, she helps you make the best of your experience during your placement at general. Very kind and thoughtful.  Assigns readings on an individual basis, relevent to your experiences during clinical. Make sure you do these readings, she will find the time to discuss with you the next day.

Clinical at the general which was great, lets you go into eating disorder program and ECT if you are motivated and a positive person. Likes to use the book, helps a lot with repetition with material in class. Lets you do work independently, disorganized in her organized way, not AMAZING but she's good :)
